pinkskulls








Level 3  Contributor 


17 reviews 


7 hotel reviews





6 helpful votes 





“Unfortunate stay”


Reviewed 1 week ago




I stayed here a few years ago and had a lovely weekend. My most recent trip wasn't as nice - here's why. My BF booked over the phone so we could have 2 rooms next to each other. He verified the rate, wrote pricing and confirmation #s and we brought them with. Once we got there, the rate had changed and we went through extensive conversation with the manager on duty to reach an agreeable rate/solution. Tip if you book over the phone, insist that they send an email confirmation so you can address any issues ahead of time. We were frustrated from the minute we checked in. On top of the price difference, our room wasn't entirely clean. We swept aside a good handful of public hairs on the bathroom floor and had open single use coffee packs for morning coffee. The air conditioner in the room was really loud and keep my BF awake on and off (I slept with earplugs and managed to sleep except when the toddler in the room next door screamed for daddy). Last, the pool was cloudy and lined with scum like it hadn't been cleaned in quite a while. I've had worse experiences, but it's too bad a place I had a good experience at a while back wasn't consistent the second time around.





Stayed June 2017, traveled with family



Sleep Quality





