tony2627



Demotte, Indiana






2 reviews 





“Fourth of July get away with allergies”


Reviewed 1 week ago




Micheal and Ryan in William B's are amazing bartenders they remember names and made sure that food was allergy free by talking to Chef Jeff who even came out to talk to us about allergies! Jessica a waitress in William B's even knew about our allergies and alerted other staff about placing food on our table that carried the allergen in it!  Never once felt like a nuisance at William B's Steakhouse. At the game Hynissa and Jessica the bartenders made sure that the chefs were aware of the allergen issues. Jonas in Nelson's Deli even went to the back to read the cake label and give me cake that had not been displayed. Bradley the security office remembered us and was constantly smiling and had such a great attitude. Nikki Thenner in housekeeping did a fantastic job making sure that our room was clean and we had plenty of towels and such. Management that helped to assure we had an allergy free trip were: Jessica in the game, Patrick in William B's, and Sherry B in food and beverage who made sure all staff was aware of allergy issues. Definitively looking forward to a return get away at Blue Chip Casino!


Room Tip: Spa Towers is where we stayed! Had security there at night to make sure random people don't go u...
