“Nice Place to Play”


Reviewed 2 weeks ago



via mobile




Nice hotels, restaurants, shops, but the casino is stingy. Fun place to spend a night or two. Just bring $$$. Restaurants range from reasonable to pricey, hotel rooms are nice, staff is friendly. Close to Lake Michigan and outlet mall.




Stayed July 2017, traveled with family



