J B



Ann Arbor, Michigan





Level 4  Contributor 


46 reviews 


15 hotel reviews





18 helpful votes 





“Quoting one room price and then charging at a much higher rate.”


Reviewed 3 weeks ago




We recently stayed at the Blue Chip Casino for 1 night. Upon check in we were told our room rate was $140. When initialing the reservation we saw the rate of $123. We just assumed that the $140 was the total with taxes. Upon check out we received a bill for $190. We immediately told them that it was incorrect. We told them we were quoted $140. They told us that the $123 was the base room rate and that they could change the rate if they felt the quoted price was wrong. Seriously? They then said that they would have to contact the clerk who checked us in (like she would even remember who we were) and they would give us a call. It has been over a week since we were there and they have not called. We have tried calling them and receive no response. Think twice before staying here. Despicable customer service. If you check the Better Business Bureau (which I just did) I was not surprised to see an "F' as their score. There are so many other places to gamble and spend the night - no need to spend your money here. Will never go back.





Stayed June 2017, traveled as a couple



Sleep Quality





Cleanliness



